#id=1
#text=Last Christmas I had to bake a cake for myself , and it was a bit of a doozy .
#id=2
#text=I do n't know a lot about making cakes , but I have a super-huge baking pan , an oven , and a big sweet tooth !
#id=3
#text=I left the house looking around various convenience stores for cake mix ; it was Christmas , so going to a big store and wasting a bunch of time was out of the question .
#id=4
#text=I had to spend a whole hour checking for a store that had any cake mix left !
#id=5
#text=I finally settled on two boxes of butter cake mix and some pink lemonade frosting and took it all home .
#id=6
#text=Since my pan was way too big for just one box , I had to follow the instructions and double every ingredient while making the batter and pouring it in .
#id=7
#text=I preheated the oven , put the cake pan with the batter in to bake , and watched TV for a few hours while I waited for it to be done .
#id=8
#text=I checked the cake several times with a toothpick to make sure it was fully baked .
#id=9
#text=Once it was done , I took it out to cool and frosted it , and then cut the cake into several square pieces .
#text=It went better than I expected for my first cake on short notice , but the frosting was SUPER sweet !
